questionsData.article:
World War One was a global conflict that took place between 1914 and 1918. Also known as the Great War
or First World War. (It 1) took place mainly in Europe, but it was spread to the Middle East, Africa and Asia.
Most of the war was fought using artillery (large weapons such as cannons), machine guns, and rifles. But the
conflict also featured bombing attacks, the use of poison gas, and saw the introduction of (new 2) technology such
as tanks, military aircrafts, and submarines. What was different about this war was the (huge 3) number of people
involved. Soldiers fought and died in millions. It was expected that the entire population would help in making
more weapons to support the war, but no one helped as it was expected. World War One was the first conflict that
was fought on worldwide scale.
